general_comment:
Great work so far on implementing your PID controller! However, your car did leave the road and so there is still some work in terms of tuning further that can be done. I have provided a reference to help with this.

Keep up the hard work and stay Udacious!

rubric.description:
What should the student demonstrate?

The student should demonstrate they know how to make a PID controller and tune the Kp, Ki, Kd values (coefficients for the controller) such that the vehicle safely drives around the track.

There's a second component to the project, being the variability of the speed. The speed limit was greatly increased from the behavioral cloning project, 30mph to 100mph. There is NO REQUIREMENT on the speed the student can pass the track on. This is meant to be an extra fun part. The student might to make an additional PID controller for the speed.

What will they submit?

The student will submit a fork of the repo: https://github.com/udacity/CarND-Controls-PID.

What should the reviewer have?

As the reviewer you have the appropriate version of the [simulator](https://github.com/udacity/CarND-PID-Control-Project/releases) and uWebSockets, https://github.com/uWebSockets/uWebSockets installed. More information on this is available on the project page.
